{
  "id": "L25",
  "title": "A Casual Birthday Party ('Borrel')",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Welcome to a Dutch birthday party, or 'borrel'! First, let's learn how to congratulate the host."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V01",
      "data": {
        "De verjaardag": "The birthday"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Gefeliciteerd met je verjaardag",
        "meaning": "Congratulations on your birthday"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L25_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Gefeliciteerd",
        "phonetic": "ge-fe-li-si-teerd",
        "tip": "The 'g' in Dutch is a sound made in the back of your throat. It's a bit like clearing your throat softly."  
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V02",
      "data": {
        "Een cadeau": "A gift"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dit is voor jou",
        "meaning": "This is for you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dank je wel",
        "meaning": "Thank you very much"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Now, let's see how to ask for something politely. You'll need this to get a drink."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Pardon",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V03",
      "data": {
        "Een glas": "A glass"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Kun je mij een glas geven?",
        "meaning": "Can you give me a glass?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ja, natuurlijk",
        "meaning": "Yes, of course"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L25_S01",
      "title": "Arrival and Greetings",
      "setting": "You've arrived at the party for your classmate, Lisa. You see her and go to say hello. Her friend Alex is at the drinks table.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Congratulate the host",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo! Fijn dat je er bent."
        },
        {
          "title": "Give your gift",
          "chatbot_message": "Dank je wel!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask for a glass",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo."
        },
        {
          "title": "Finish the interaction",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, natuurlijk. Alsjeblieft."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! Now you have a drink. Let's learn how to join a conversation and introduce yourself."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik ben...",
        "meaning": "I am..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V04",
      "data": {
        "Kennen": "To know (a person)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L25_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "kennen",
        "phonetic": "ken-nen",
        "tip": "This sounds different from 'kunnen' (can). 'Kennen' has a short 'e' sound, like in the English word 'ken'." 
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V05",
      "data": {
        "Ik ken": "I know"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V06",
      "data": {
        "Jij kent": "You know"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Hoe ken jij Lisa?",
        "meaning": "How do you know Lisa?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V07",
      "data": {
        "De studie": "The study / school"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ik ken Lisa van de studie",
        "meaning": "I know Lisa from my studies"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L25_S02",
      "title": "Joining a Conversation",
      "setting": "You see Alex, who gave you the glass, talking with another guest, Maria. You decide to join them.",       
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Introduce yourself",
          "chatbot_message": "Hoi! Ik ben Alex.",
          "extract_info": {
            "user_name": "Extract the user's name from their message"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask how they know Lisa",
          "chatbot_message": "Hallo {user_name}. Ik ben Maria."
        },
        {
          "title": "Explain how you know Lisa",
          "chatbot_message": "Ik ken Lisa van de studie. En jij? Hoe ken jij Lisa?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Finish the conversation",
          "chatbot_message": "Ah, leuk!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Well done! Mingling is key at a 'borrel'. Now, let's learn how to politely leave a conversation and then the party."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Het was leuk om met je te praten",
        "meaning": "It was nice to talk to you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V08",
      "data": {
        "Ik ga": "I am going"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V09",
      "data": {
        "De uitnodiging": "The invitation"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L25_V10",
      "data": {
        "Het feestje": "The party"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Bedankt voor de uitnodiging",
        "meaning": "Thank you for the invitation"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Het was een leuk feestje",
        "meaning": "It was a nice party"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L25_E13",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Doei",
        "meaning": "Bye (informal)"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L25_S03",
      "title": "Saying Goodbye",
      "setting": "You've talked for a bit and now you want to mingle more before leaving the party. First, you exit the conversation with Alex and Maria. Then, you find Lisa to say goodbye.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Politely exit the conversation",
          "chatbot_message": "Ja, de studie is interessant."
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the host for the party",
          "chatbot_message": "Ok√©! Doei!"
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Graag gedaan!"
        },
        {
          "title": "End the lesson",
          "chatbot_message": "Doei!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}